Description: APRS daemon for packet radio operations
 aprstx is a comprehensive APRS (Automatic Packet Reporting System) daemon
 written in Rust. It supports multiple TNC interfaces, APRS-IS connectivity,
 smart beaconing, digipeating, and GPS integration.
 .
 Features include:
  - Multiple serial port TNC support (KISS and TNC2 protocols)
  - APRS-IS network connectivity
  - Smart beaconing with configurable parameters
  - Digipeater functionality with viscous delay
  - GPS support (serial NMEA, GPSD, or fixed position)
  - Message handling with acknowledgments
  - Flexible packet filtering
  - Pure Rust implementation without system dependencies